        {
            "id": "action",
            "instance": "f7f3aaf6-44e3-4558-b618-d547db312ff1",
            "properties": [
                [
                    "name",
                    "External Remote Services"
                ],
                [
                    "ttp",
                    [
                        [
                            "tactic",
                            "TA0001"
                        ],
                        [
                            "technique",
                            "T1133"
                        ]
                    ]
                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "Following initial access via phishing, credential theft, or exploitation, Cl0p affiliates authenticate to internet-exposed remote access services — including VPN gateways, RDP endpoints, and remote management platforms — to establish a persistent, authenticated tunnel into the internal network. Valid stolen credentials enable direct access to these services, bypassing perimeter controls and providing a stable foothold from which to conduct hands-on-keyboard operations. External remote services are used in conjunction with all other initial access vectors, serving as the pivot point into internal network segments including the login node, management infrastructure, enterprise systems, and HPC compute environments."
                ],
                [
                    "confidence",
                    null
                ],
                [
                    "execution_start",
                    null
                ],
                [
                    "execution_end",
                    null
                ]
            ],
